<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<text id="02-output-contract" title="Web Scraping Pagination Output Contract" version="1.0.0" est_tokens="800" depth="essential">
  <summary>JSON Schema for the per-walk report. Captures pagination pattern, pages walked, items collected, duplicate count, and pool high-water mark.</summary>

  <section title="JSON Schema (draft-07)">
    <code lang="json"><![CDATA[
{
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
  "$id": "https://faion.net/schemas/web-scraping-pagination.json",
  "type": "object",
  "required": ["artefact_id", "source", "pattern", "pages_walked", "items_collected", "duplicate_count", "concurrency_cap", "pool_high_water_mark", "version", "last_reviewed"],
  "properties": {
    "artefact_id":          {"type": "string", "pattern": "^wsp-[a-z0-9-]{6,}$"},
    "source":               {"type": "string", "minLength": 1},
    "pattern":              {"enum": ["next-button", "infinite-scroll", "load-more"]},
    "pages_walked":         {"type": "integer", "minimum": 1},
    "items_collected":      {"type": "integer", "minimum": 0},
    "duplicate_count":      {"type": "integer", "minimum": 0},
    "concurrency_cap":      {"type": "integer", "minimum": 1, "maximum": 50},
    "pool_high_water_mark": {"type": "integer", "minimum": 0},
    "stop_condition_observed": {"type": "string"},
    "verdict":              {"enum": ["approve", "block-wrong-pattern", "block-no-dedupe", "block-unbounded-concurrency"]},
    "version":              {"type": "string", "pattern": "^\\d+\\.\\d+\\.\\d+$"},
    "last_reviewed":        {"type": "string", "format": "date"}
  }
}
]]></code>
  </section>

  <example valid="true">
    <code lang="json"><![CDATA[
{
  "artefact_id": "wsp-news-walk-2026-05-23",
  "source": "example.com/news",
  "pattern": "infinite-scroll",
  "pages_walked": 12,
  "items_collected": 240,
  "duplicate_count": 18,
  "concurrency_cap": 3,
  "pool_high_water_mark": 3,
  "stop_condition_observed": "scrollHeight stable for 4s",
  "verdict": "approve",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "last_reviewed": "2026-05-23"
}
]]></code>
  </example>

  <example valid="false">
    <code lang="json"><![CDATA[
{
  "artefact_id": "walk",
  "source": "example.com/news",
  "pattern": "next-button",
  "pages_walked": 1000,
  "items_collected": 20000,
  "duplicate_count": 0,
  "concurrency_cap": 100,
  "pool_high_water_mark": 87,
  "verdict": "approve",
  "version": "1.0",
  "last_reviewed": "today"
}
]]></code>
    <note>artefact_id missing wsp- prefix; pages_walked=1000 unreasonable for next-button (likely infinite loop); duplicate_count=0 with 20k items suggests dedupe was skipped (r3 violation); concurrency_cap=100 exceeds maximum 50; pool_high_water_mark=87 is consistent with cap=100 — symptom of unbounded concurrency; version + last_reviewed malformed.</note>
  </example>

  <section title="Forbidden patterns">
    <antipattern>
      <description>verdict=approve with concurrency_cap &gt; 10 unless explicitly justified.</description>
      <reason>Aggressive concurrency raises ban risk and OOM risk; default cap is 3.</reason>
    </antipattern>
    <antipattern>
      <description>verdict=approve with pool_high_water_mark &gt; concurrency_cap.</description>
      <reason>Indicates leaked pages — finally-close is not effective.</reason>
    </antipattern>
    <antipattern>
      <description>duplicate_count=0 when pattern=infinite-scroll AND items_collected &gt; 50.</description>
      <reason>Infinite-scroll overlaps by design; zero duplicates means dedupe was skipped (r3 violation).</reason>
    </antipattern>
  </section>

  <reference path="templates/web-scraping-pagination.json">Schema canonical location.</reference>
  <reference path="scripts/validate-web-scraping-pagination.py">Validator that enforces this contract.</reference>
</text>
